      <item>
        <title>My .css file doesnt work</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/cinowini">@cinowini</a></p>
<p>Welcome to the Frontity community. Great to see that you’re trying out Frontity.</p>
<p>You’re importing your CSS from <code>Header.css</code> but not storing it in a variable that you can reference. You need to do something like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">import bootstrapCss from 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
const BootstrapStyles = () =&gt; (
  &lt;Global styles={css(bootstrapCss)} /&gt;
);
</code></pre>
<p>The above code snippet is from <strong><a href="https://github.com/frontity-demos/bootstrap-theme-demo/blob/4166566355b2490a4ac2ea1968ce08e2d9540ceb/packages/bootstrap-theme/src/components/Theme/index.js">this file</a></strong> in <strong><a href="https://github.com/frontity-demos/bootstrap-theme-demo">this repo</a></strong> in case you want to dig in to this further.</p>
<p>Hope this helps.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/my-css-file-doesnt-work/2896/4">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
